@philritz1 And the most powerful and wealthy individuals have a correlated impact when they act in their own self interest.
When individuals act in their own self-interest without considering the impact on the greater good and the future, the result can be disastrous for everyone.
The resource is destroyed, and everyone suffers as a result.This concept applies to many different areas, from overfishing in the ocean to climate change caused by carbon emissions.

For example, imagine a group of farmers who all share a common grazing field. Each farmer wants to maximize their own profits, so they all add more and more cows to the field. But eventually, the field becomes overgrazed and can no longer support all the cows.
Here's the basic idea: the tragedy of the commons occurs when a shared resource is overexploited because individuals acting in their own self-interest end up destroying the resource for everyone.
